Pyweek 10 - "Wibble Wobble"
Team: __pyweeklings__
Game: Wabble

Prerequisites:

    Pyglet 1.1.4 or SVN (see troubleshooting) http://www.pyglet.org/download.html
    
    AVBin:
        Windows: Extract avbin.dll next to run_game.py
            http://avbin.googlecode.com/files/avbin-win32-5.zip
            
        Linux: Run install.sh
            http://avbin.googlecode.com/files/avbin-linux-x86-32-7.tar.gz


How to Run:
    Execute run_game.py from the console
    
                   or

    Double-click run_game.pyw


How to Play:
    Use the arrow keys to move the 'Blob monster'
    
    Get the pink Blobules to increase score


**************************************************************************
**************************************************************************
**                                                                      **
**         !         T R O U B L E S H O O T I N G            !         **
**                                                                      **
**************************************************************************
**************************************************************************

EVERYONE:  The best advice is, if you're using Pyglet 1.1.4 and something
           goes wrong, install the SVN. If you're using SVN and something
           goes wrong, install 1.1.4. Please try this before rating DNW!


                              WINDOWS
                              
NO SOUND : Did you install AVBin?

GRAPHIC CORRUPTION : Install Pyglet 1.1.4

                               LINUX
STUDDERING : Sound issue. Does run_game_silent.py speed things up? If so
             install Pyglet SVN.    